snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a Hindu but I don't need to say that before expressing my love for other religions. Yes, I love this song and I love & deeply respect every religion.

Edit: Many people are saying it's Hamad or Naat and not a song. Thank you all for letting me know this. When something touches the heart, it is always unnamed and ineffable; it is only later that we name it and put it into a language. Different people, cultures, and religions may call it by different names, yet we all feel what it is trying to express, even if we do not speak the same language. We're all connected with the same thread. 

Love you all!
